      "latex": "",
      "raw": "Standard amortized monthly payment: \\\\[ PMT = P \\\\, \\\\cdot \\\\, \\\\frac{i(1+i)^{n}}{(1+i)^{n}-1} \\\\] where \\\\(P\\\\) is principal, \\\\(i = \\\\tfrac{APR}{12}\\\\) is the monthly rate, and \\\\(n\\\\) the number of months. Remaining total interest for a loan is: \\\\[ I_{total} = PMT \\\\cdot n - P \\\\] Break-even months approximate when cumulative savings exceed upfront costs \\\\(C\\\\): \\\\[ m_{BE} \\\\approx \\\\min\\\\{m : \\\\sum_{k=1}^{m} (PMT_{old}-PMT_{new}) \\\\ge C\\\\} \\\\] (In this tool we compute break-even via a monthly cumulative comparison; if costs are rolled into the new principal, interest on those costs is reflected in \\\\(PMT_{new}\\\\).)"
    }
  ],
